We recommended that:
Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to prepare and submit an updated Certified list of taxpayers, bearing the names, amount due and collectible during the year, and submit the same to the accounting unit as the basis in the setting up of RPT/SEF tax receivable in the succeeding year;
Require the Accountant to –
Use the Certified List of Taxpayers prepared by the Office of the Municipal Treasurer as the basis in recording the RPT/SEF Tax Receivables at the beginning of the year.
Exert extra effort to determine the correct amount of prepayments of RPT/SET, which should be reflected as balances of the accounts “Deferred RPT/SET”;
Make the necessary adjustments in the books for the realized portion of the Deferred RPT/SET;
Prioritize the establishment of subsidiary ledgers for the respective amounts;
Make the necessary adjustments to reclassify the items included in the Other Payables account to the appropriate FS accounts, to present a more reliable and accurate Financial Statements;
Exert extra effort for the collection of the receivable;
Reconcile and analyze the dormant accounts to determine whether they warrant adjustment or write-off in accordance with existing COA rules and regulations;
Furnish certification and/or reasons why the books of accounts/records/financial statements/schedules and supporting documents cannot be located; and
Require proper turn-over of documents/pending work from officials and employees retiring/separating from officials and employees retiring/separating from office/service to ensure completeness of records.

